00:16:14,291 --> 00:16:16,625
Stuff like that.
- [sighs]

230
00:16:16,708 --> 00:16:18,458
No.
- Come on!

231
00:16:18,541 --> 00:16:20,208
Now's not the time
to be heartless.

232
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:22,208
- Not the time to be a
chicken,
either.

233
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:23,791
If you wanna know how he is,

234
00:16:23,875 --> 00:16:25,666
go check yourself.
You're a big girl.

235
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:30,958
- He was in love with her,
and now -- now she's gone,

236
00:16:31,041 --> 00:16:34,125
and Kousei is empty inside.

237
00:16:34,208 --> 00:16:37,041
I want to help him,
but I have no idea what to do.

238
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:39,875
- How are you so dumb?

239
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:41,166
If your friend is crying
on the floor,

240
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:43,750
you don't run out and buy him
a new handkerchief.

241
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:46,541
You give him your sleeve.
- Easy as that, huh?

242
00:16:46,625 --> 00:16:50,041
- Listen, I don't think it has
to be some grand gesture.

243
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:52,625
I think that it's all right
to just be you.

244
00:16:52,708 --> 00:16:54,125
For innings like this,

245
00:16:54,208 --> 00:16:55,583
you bench your head
for a while

246
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:56,833
and let your heart pitch.

247
00:16:56,916 --> 00:16:58,833
- [gasps]

248
00:16:58,916 --> 00:17:01,666
How did you get so smart
about relationship stuff?

249
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,833
- Boys love.
[laughs]

250
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,250
<i>- When my lie finally brought</i>
<i>the two of us together,</i>

251
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:10,500
<i>you were different</i>
<i>than I'd imagined.</i>

252
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:13,875
<i>Stubborn and passive</i>
<i>and pessimistic,</i>

253
00:17:13,958 --> 00:17:17,041
<i>not to mention the fact</i>
<i>that you stole my leggings.</i>

254
00:17:17,125 --> 00:17:19,125
<i>Your voice was lower</i>
<i>than I thought.</i>

255
00:17:19,208 --> 00:17:20,708
<i>You were a guy,</i>
<i>you know?</i>

256
00:17:20,791 --> 00:17:24,833
<i>And you were gentle.</i>
<i>No surprise there.</i>

257
00:17:26,375 --> 00:17:28,208
<i>Remember when we jumped off</i>
<i>that bridge?</i>

258
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:30,916
<i>The river water felt amazing.</i>

259
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,458
<i>And the moon shining down</i>
<i>at the music room,</i>

260
00:17:33,541 --> 00:17:36,375
<i>like we could grab it</i>
<i>on our tiptoes.</i>

261
00:17:36,458 --> 00:17:38,166
<i>When we raced that train,</i>

262
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:40,750
<i>I really thought we could win.</i>

263
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,958
<i>Singing "Twinkle, Twinkle</i>
<i>Little Star" with you</i>

264
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:46,125
<i>late at night</i>
<i>felt kinda perfect.</i>

265
00:17:46,208 --> 00:17:49,125
<i>Being at school after dark,</i>
<i>it's mysterious, right?</i>

266
00:17:49,208 --> 00:17:53,041
<i>And snow, it looks like</i>
<i>cherry blossom petals.</i>

267
00:17:53,125 --> 00:17:55,041
<i>You must think I'm silly,</i>

268
00:17:55,125 --> 00:17:58,000
<i>finding wonder in the everyday</i>
<i>things around us.</i>

269
00:17:58,083 --> 00:17:58,583
<i>Things I saw with you.</i>

270
00:18:01,791 --> 00:18:04,875
<i>- Look at you,</i>
<i>playing it with such nuance.</i>

271
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,708
<i>You're grown-up, kiddo.</i>

272
00:18:06,791 --> 00:18:08,291
<i>- You're so cool!</i>

273
00:18:08,375 --> 00:18:09,583
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

274
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:12,416
- [gasps]
I'm just smiling and blushing

275
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:14,000
'cause it's a pretty song.
That's all!

276
00:18:14,083 --> 00:18:17,375
Falling for my brother's rival
would be such a cliché!

277
00:18:17,458 --> 00:18:19,833
<i>- Isn't it funny how</i>
<i>the most unforgettable scenes</i>

278
00:18:19,916 --> 00:18:22,916
<i>can be so trivial</i>
<i>and vice-versa?</i>

279
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,833
<i>- None of it was trivial.</i>

280
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:27,541
- So what's the verdict?

281
00:18:27,625 --> 00:18:28,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

282
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:32,208
Was I able to live
inside someone's heart?

283
00:18:32,291 --> 00:18:33,750
<i>- No question.</i>

284
00:18:33,833 --> 00:18:36,583
- And this heart,
it wouldn't happen to be yours,

285
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:37,875
would it?

286
00:18:37,958 --> 00:18:40,166
<i>- You barged in</i>
<i>without knocking.</i>

287
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:41,958
- Do you think that
you'll remember me a little

288
00:18:42,041 --> 00:18:44,750
from time to time?

289
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:45,625
- Got no choice.

290
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:47,375
<i>You'd come back to haunt me.</i>

291
00:18:47,458 --> 00:18:50,291
- No hitting the reset button.

292
00:18:50,375 --> 00:18:51,875
- Not ever.

293
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:53,750
- Don't you forget me.

294
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,041
- [grunts]

295
00:18:55,125 --> 00:18:58,125
- That's a promise, okay?
- Mm-hmm.

296
00:18:58,208 --> 00:19:02,083
- I'm glad we found each other.

297
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:04,208
Will I reach you?

298
00:19:04,291 --> 00:19:06,000
I hope I can.

299
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:08,041
<i>[Wacci's "Kirameki"]</i>

300
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:10,166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

301
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:13,458
Here's the truth, Kousei.

302
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:16,500
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

303
00:19:16,583 --> 00:19:18,416
- I love you!

304
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:21,250
